<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-09-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="93" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Mizner</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-09-12"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 12,
                            1890</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Wharton requests Mr. Ryan to telegraph to Mr. Mizner that this Government
                        is much gratified to learn of the complete compliance by the two belligerent
                        powers in Central America with the bases of peace and of the disbanding of
                        the two armies, and to instruct him to express the earnest wishes of the
                        United States for continued friendliness between Guatemala and Salvador and
                        for their undisturbed prosperity.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>